## Observations

1. step curve binary as expected: 1.00 until t=T_cold, jumps to 2.00.
2. linear curve smooth ramp 1.04 -> 1.94 over [0, T_cold).
3. sigmoid curve S-shape: slow start (1.07 at t=3), accelerates around
   the midpoint (1.40 at t=6), saturates near T_cold (1.99 at t=13).
4. All three converge to 2.00 at t >= T_cold.
5. The actual K8s readiness probe success came at t=35.3s, more than 2x
   the configured T_cold. This validates the need for profile_cold_start.py
   to measure T_cold per service in the target cluster rather than relying
   on literature-based estimates.

## Bug found and fixed in this smoke

f_sigmoid was reporting 2.01 at t > T_cold while step and linear correctly
reported 2.00. The unclamped affine sigmoid keeps growing past 1.0 because
the canonical sigmoid is unbounded. Fix committed as commit 63a6366: clamp
f_sigmoid to [0, 1] for t outside [0, T_cold]. Two regression tests added
to test_effective_capacity.py.
